data.description:
Beautifully updated home with a coast feel.  As you step into the home you will walk into a spacious great room with vaulted ceiling and wood burning fireplace. The kitchen has been remodeled in the last 3 years with lots of custom cabinets with all kinds of cool features. No idea was left off.  Most cabinets have pull out shelves, corner area where lazy Susan would be are two shelves that completely pull out so that you can reach everything.  Kitchen island has power, a shelf that pulls out and up and becomes a cutting board, there is also a cabinet to store the garbage cans.  After you look at the cabinets notice the gorgeous Quartz counter tops and then look up and see beach feel ship lapped kitchen and breakfast ceiling. 
Both bathrooms have been updated.  Primary bathroom has a high double vanity , a walk in shower and a soaking tub.  Primary bedroom is large size with a enormous walk in closet.  Front bedroom is spacious with high ceiling.  3rd bedroom was a bedroom and separate bonus room.  Wall was taken down to make room for a live at home college student so that he could his own space.  Put the wall back up and have a 4 bedroom home or leave it down for a perfect room for a live in grandparent. 
Step out back to a nice long entertaining deck with a lattice area for a hot tub fire pit or just chairs for visiting.  Fenced yard and shed remains.  No flood insurance required.  Close to Ocean Springs middle and high school
